# Use CSS variables

Use CSS variables for theme colors when setting `color` or any other use of color in the frontend. The light or dark theme is applied to CSS variables on page load and kept up to date.

<rule>
name: use_css_vars
description: Use CSS variables for MUI component colors and elsewhere
filters:
  # Match any .tsx files
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.tsx$"

actions:
  - type: reject
    conditions:
      # Match "color: " followed by *not* "var(--color-name)"
      - pattern: "[Cc]olor: \"(?!var(--[a-zA-Z0-9-]+)\").*"
        message: "Do not use MaterialUI color names directly. Use a `var(--color-name) equivalent from the list of recognized names."

  - type: suggest
    message: |
      The following CSS variables are recognized:
        var(--bg-primary)
        var(--bg-paper)
        var(--text-primary)
        var(--text-on-primary)
        var(--text-secondary)
        var(--gradient-text)
        var(--seventy-percent-opacity)
        var(--twenty-percent-opacity)
        var(--twelve-percent-opacity)
        var(--five-percent-opacity)

examples:
  - input: |
      # Bad: Standard MUI theme color
      color: "text-secondary"

      # Good: Use CSS variable
      color: var(--text-secondary)
    output: "Correctly used CSS variable"

metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.0
</rule>
